ipt Records\n\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item\nis one redacted JSON transcript record with only per-record data:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n\t\"record_index\": 0,\n\t\"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n\t\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T09:08:43.427Z\",\n\t\"event_kind\": \"response_item\",\n\t\"role\": \"assistant\",\n\t\"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n\t\"tool_name\": null,\n\t\"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSlim normalized fields support timeline browsing and handoff without reparsing\nevery provider-specific record:\n\n- `event_kind`: provider event type, with a nested event type when obvious\n- `role` and `content_text`: conversation body when extraction is obvious\n- `tool_name`: obvious tool activity\n- `source_record`: redacted provider record for provenance and future adapters\n\nOmit repeated session/source metadata from each transcript record. Also omit git\nbranch, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, and turn ids from\ntop-level record fields.\n\nRecord hashes and dedupe use the original trimmed JSONL bytes, not the redacted\ntranscript record.\n\n## Deduplication\n\nUse stable record hashes:\n\n```text\nsha256(trimmed raw JSONL line bytes)\n```\n\nThe session-level `record-hashes` set tracks source-record dedupe. Transcript append\ndedupe is rebuilt from the stored transcript list by reading each record's\n`record_hash`. This keeps transcript backfill possible if the list is missing\nwhile the record hash set still exists.\n\n## Future Association Model\n\nDo not attach transcript data directly to branches, commits, changes, or pull\nrequests in the POC. The project session is the durable object.\n\nLater, when GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-10T07:20:27.889Z","type":"response_item","payload